<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefdc46bc-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6013"><num value="6013">§ 6013.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idefdc46bd-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6013/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year such sums as are necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idefdc46be-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6013/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Funds appropriated to carry out this chapter shall not be available for payment of the expenses or expenditures of the Board in administering any provision of any plan issued under this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idefdc46bf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/624/tXIX/s1918">Pub. L. 101–624, title XIX, § 1918</ref>, <date date="1990-11-28">Nov. 28, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/3854">104 Stat. 3854</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
